H3.text: Vendredi is French for which day of the week. TGIFF

A5.text: The word for Friday in most Romance languages is derived from Latin dies Veneris or 'day of Venus' (a translation of Greek Aphrodī́tēs hēméra, Ἀφροδῑ́της Ἡμέρα), such as vendredi in French, venres in Galician, divendres in Catalan, vennari in Corsican, venerdì in Italian, vineri in Romanian, and viernes in Spanish
